withering vine<br>
-------------------------------------------------------------------<br>
<br>
Creapiing collapsed again. She lay at the feet of her enemy, incapable of defending herself. The Pale elf before her grinned down upon her and spat on her. You are worthless, there exists no place for you in the light. As she lay helpless on the ground her mind raged with anger that could find no outlet from her crumpled form. Then slowly the effect faded, and as she felt her energy return she drew from the hate that had been building to leap to her feet and impale the insipid elf before her. He died far too quickly, hardly registering his own death before it came from her sword.<br>
<br>
These spells had been coming upon her more and more often. She had destroyed all her furnishings, had her home and her office gutted, and yet she could not find the source of the poison that was slowly eating away at her. The precious books, art, and antique furniture that had adorned her office were long since burned, and yet she was slowly becoming more and more helpless. Her long years of training with the rogues allowed her to recognize all the symptoms and soon enough she would start to lose her judgement.<br>
<br>
Only a few days before, Creapiing had met with Khasirath, the Thresher of the Harvest, and begged him to slay her if she did not find the source of this poison soon. Soon I will lose all my mental abilities as well as having more and more frequent collapses. If I do not find the source of this poison I ask you to kill me. Do not give me much more time, and do not wait for me to ask again. I ask you as the Thresher to show me some mercy for my service to Innoruuk and slay me quickly and before I get any worse.<br>
<br>
Khasirath gazed deeply into the eyes of Creapiing and responded with the only answer a Teir’dal could give. Creapiing, I would gladly slay every druid in Norrath than to hurt you, but it is my duty and my honor to be the one to kill you should the day come that you can no longer benefit the Harvest. I promise to be swift and send you to the father with haste.<br>
<br>
Creapiing saw the look that briefly crossed Khasirath’s face, noted it, and nodded. He would slay her before she became a hazard to the Violent Harvest. Creapiing bowed and smiled the smile of one who is has nothing to lose. Khasirath, the father asks much of us all.<br>
